@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam defaultFontColor #E0E0E0
skinparam arrowColor #E0E0E0
skinparam participantBorderColor #E0E0E0
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #2B2B2B
skinparam databaseBorderColor #E0E0E0
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #2B2B2B
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #E0E0E0
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBackgroundColor #444444
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #333333
skinparam noteBorderColor #E0E0E0
skinparam noteFontColor #E0E0E0

title BatterySentinel: Multi-Device Synchronization

participant "Device A\n(e.g., Tablet)" as DevA
database "Local DataStore\n(Device A)" as DS_A
participant "Firebase\nCloud Function" as Cloud
participant "FCM\n(Firebase Cloud Messaging)" as FCM
participant "Device B\n(e.g., Smartphone)" as DevB

note over DevA: Battery drops\nbelow 20%
DevA -> DevA: Fire Local Notification
DevA -> DS_A: Save "Triggered" State (Synchronous)
note over DevA, DS_A: Prevents duplicates if killed\nduring the network call

DevA -> Cloud: notifyOtherDevices()\n(Auth: Google Sign-In)
activate Cloud
Cloud -> Cloud: Verify Auth & Rate Limit\n(Max 50/day)
Cloud -> Cloud: Query Firestore for\nother registered devices
Cloud -> FCM: Send High-Priority\nData Message
deactivate Cloud

FCM -> DevB: Deliver FCM Message
activate DevB
DevB -> DevB: FcmService wakes up
DevB -> DevB: Format Message\n("Tablet - 20%")
DevB -> DevB: Fire Remote Notification
deactivate DevB
@enduml
